OL,3,C'Unreserved apology' offered after
OL,4,Cwrongful rape conviction
OL,6,F"There may have been a belief that I
OL,7,Fhave been unwilling ever to apologise
OL,8,Fto Mr Malkinson, and I want to clarify
OL,9,Fthat this is not the case.
OL,11,F"For me, offering a genuine apology
OL,12,Frequired a clear understanding of the
OL,13,Fcircumstances in which the commission
OL,14,Ffailed Mr Malkinson. We now have that.
OL,16,F"Nobody can ever begin to imagine the
OL,17,Fdevastating impact that Mr Malkinson's
OL,18,Fwrongful conviction has had on his
OL,19,Flife, and I can only apologise for the
OL,20,Fadditional harm caused to him by our
OL,21,Fhandling of his case."
